HEADWORD: Subreader
<hw>Sub*read"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>An under reader in the inns of court, who reads the texts of law
the reader is to discourse upon.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

